# Pi Codex Account Pool

Standalone local alpha package for a Pi `0.80.6` extension. OAuth enrollment and automatic session credential refresh are wired; quota and reset-credit mutation are not.

## Decisions

- Override the existing `openai-codex` stream handler while preserving Pi's native model catalog and provider identity.
- Keep `openai-codex/gpt-5.6-sol` as the selected model; only inject the selected profile access token as `options.apiKey`.
- Do not use a synthetic provider ID: Pi's Codex conversion logic keys tool-call ID handling on the built-in provider identity.
- Store only secret-free profile metadata on disk with `0600` permissions.
- Keep OAuth credentials behind `CredentialStore`: native macOS Keychain first, with per-profile `0600` files as a fallback when background launchd sessions are denied Keychain interaction.
- Retry once only for exact structured `usage_limit_reached` before meaningful output.
- Do not rotate for generic 429, auth, transport, or model errors.
- Decode email/account labels from JWT claims without logging raw JWTs.
- Enroll additional accounts with an expected email; reject a browser session authenticated as the wrong account before writing Keychain or metadata.
- Preserve Pi's current native `openai-codex` OAuth credential before adding another account.
- Refresh expiring OAuth credentials through OpenAI's refresher and persist rotated credentials back through the active `CredentialStore` backend.
- Read quota through `GET https://chatgpt.com/backend-api/wham/usage` in future live wiring; tests mock fetch only.

## Next live slice

Wire `/codex-pool-refresh` to the quota client, then add explicit account pin/remove controls. Reset-credit mutation stays explicit and separate. Fleet rollout still requires central cross-host refresh and lease serialization.
